TS Galaxy’s recent resurgence is showing little signs of letting up. The Rockets continued their strong run of form in the DStv Premiership when they defeated Bloemfontein Celtic 1-0 at the Mbombela Stadium in Nelspruit on Wednesday. Lindokuhle Mbatha scored the only goal of the game to help the Mpumalanga outfit earn their third win from their last five matches. Owen Da Gama’s charges climbed up to ninth on the log above Kaizer Chiefs and their opponents Phunya Sele Sele. Their quest for a top eight finish is beginning to pick up steam.Da Gama has quickly turned the Rockets from relegation favorites to top eight challengers. And Mbatha has been key in the Rockets’ run, scoring crucial goals which have highlighted his experience. 